&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position:&lt;/strong&gt; Litigation Paralegal&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Range:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;$29.00–$37.50 per hour&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance Based Bonus:&lt;/strong&gt; bonuses tied to performance&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Health:&lt;/strong&gt; Medical (80-85% company contributes towards medical premium), Dental, Vision&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial:&lt;/strong&gt; 401(k) up to 4%company match, life insurance, commuter benefits&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Time Off: &lt;/strong&gt;Paid time off, paid holidays, and leave in accordance with applicable law&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location / Model:&lt;/strong&gt; In-office | Chicago, Illinois&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FLSA Status:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Non-Exempt (Eligible for overtime pay)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Application Deadline:&lt;/strong&gt; Open until filled&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Johnson Law Group&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Johnson Law Group is a nationally recognized plaintiffs’ law firm headquartered in Houston, Texas, with offices across the United States and the United Kingdom. For more than 20 years, the firm has represented individuals and families in personal injury, mass tort, workers’ compensation, and complex litigation matters. We combine deep legal experience with a forward-thinking approach to technology, data, and client service. Our teams are collaborative, mission-driven, and committed to doing meaningful work that makes a difference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Johnson Law Group is seeking a Litigation Paralegal to join our Chicago office in support of our Personal Injury Auto Accidents practice. This role involves managing litigation matters from intake through trial, preparing legal documents, and ensuring compliance with procedural requirements and deadlines. Based on experience and qualifications, this position may be considered at a Senior Litigation Paralegal level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft pleadings, discovery requests and responses, subpoenas, motions, and settlement documents for attorney review&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize, review, and summarize medical records, police reports, and accident-related documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with clients, medical providers, expert witnesses, and opposing counsel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct legal and factual research to support case development and litigation strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with deposition, mediation, and trial preparation, including exhibits, witness files, and trial binders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and manage litigation deadlines in accordance with Illinois civil procedure and local court rules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate, well-organized case files within the firm’s case management system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide compassionate, professional communication to clients throughout the litigation process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Associate’s or bachelor’s degree&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of &lt;strong&gt;3 years&lt;/strong&gt; of litigation paralegal experience in personal injury (auto accident experience strongly preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong working knowledge of Illinois civil procedure and electronic filing systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational, writing, and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with Microsoft Office and legal case management software&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple priorities and work effectively in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paralegal certificate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bilingual proficiency in Spanish and English&lt;/li&gt

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;About Johnson Law Group&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Johnson Law Group (JLG) is an international claimant litigation law firm with offices in Manchester, London, Houston, Manhattan, and Chicago.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a bright and enthusiastic paralegal to join our growing team of fee earners in our Manchester office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a firm, JLG acts for consumers and businesses that have been “wronged” in some way by large corporations. We specialise in bringing large group actions against those corporations and driving high volumes of claims for financial mis-selling.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We always represent Claimants and with our U.S. roots, we bring our own style of group and volume litigation to the UK legal market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates will assist in our busy and ever-growing financial mis-selling team, as well as the day-to-day business of handling client inquiries and advising on the legal processes our clients are involved in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must be detail-oriented, possess excellent communication skills, display strong organisational skills, and keep a professional appearance. Candidates must also thrive under pressure when communicating with clients and have an ability to calmly articulate areas of discussion and the missions of Johnson Law Group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous fee earning experience preferred but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements (Must Have)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Careful attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to understand and follow documented processes and procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to prioritise and multi-task&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High level of professionalism&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills, both persuasive and objective&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in all MS Office applications, including Excel, Outlook, and Word.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Critical thinking and problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to thrive in a team environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Law Degree (2.1 or above)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience working in a law firm as a legal clerk in a fee earning capacity (preferably in civil/commercial litigation or financial mis-selling)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Request, chase, organise, review, and report on Data Subject Access Requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Update and liaise with clients by phone and in writing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain up-to-date diary and task lists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regularly and effectively chase outstanding tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively progress cases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist fee earners with tasks on their cases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft and prepare claims for submission to the Financial Ombudsman Service (FOS), Financial Services Compensation Scheme (FSCS), and for court issue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft letters of advice, witness statements, and collate relevant disclosure documents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyse limitation issues on cases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Carry out case law research and report findings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide excellent customer service and communicate with clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;e-File in the High Court and County Court&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clearly document all information in the case management system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and meet all procedural, limitation, and court deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide status updates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
